commitResults.messageTitle: Duke now greets with a welcome message
Duke now greets and processes commands (echo or exit)
Add command storage and retrieval capability to Duke
Add task status tracking capability to Duke
commitResults.messageBody: Duke can now mark tasks as done, and reflect the status of the task (done or not done) whilst printing the list of tasks. Created a new class 'Task' for better encapsulation. Text encoding for 'Task Status Icon' fishy in my machine (IDE prints question marks instead of unicode characters), but the logic of the code is present.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add capability to handle various types of events.
commitResults.messageBody: These events includes todos, deadlines, and events.

commitResults.messageTitle: Enable Duke to handle errors concerning badly formatted commands.
Add support for deleting tasks and handling more errroneous input cases.
commitResults.messageBody: At level 6, Duke is now able to manage three different types of tasks - todos, deadlines, and events. Duke can add, delete and change the 'done' status of these tasks. She can also inform the user when they have entered an incorrect command, input in a wrong format, or an unreasonable query. While Duke can perform these basic functions now, there remains scpe for improvement. For instance, instead of using switch statements to toggle between handling of different commands, perhaps enums might offer a more efficient way. Furthermore, all testing done on Duke has been entirely manual - I/O redirection to perform semi-automated testing might be another logical direction to extend this project in.
